    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e99c0776_2069f431",
        "filename": "docs/ANDROID-EMULATION-LIBRARY.TXT",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 185,
      "author": {
        "id": 1079748
      },
      "writtenOn": "2015-09-18T18:10:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think we should change our mental picture of the build\n\nCurrent situation:\n- top level target is external/qemu/ (this is a mash-up of qemu1 and AndroieEmu)\n- This uses scripts (manually launched) to create and use external/qemu-android/ prebuilts if desired.\n\nIn the new world, this is no longer the case.\n- There are two top level targets: external/qemu1 and external/qemu2. \n  - Pick which one you want. \n  - If you want both, build both. Neither depends on the other, and should not pull the other.\n  - If there is common code (like the launcher that decides which qemu to launch, it belongs in AndroidEmu).\n- Both of them require AndroidEmu.\n- You *could* use a script in both external/qemu1/ and external/qemu2 to (re)build and pull AndroidEmu library, but it\u0027d be better if we can go the Android.mk way (top level Makefiles with includes) as that gives the best incremental builds and we\u0027re likely to hack on the AndroidEmu library hand-in-hand with one or both of qemu{1,2}.",
      "parentUuid": "69dad736_c08a009d",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 185,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 185,
        "endChar": 68
      },
      "revId": "b045c6127554eb0575023f042891a03d5e1e88f6",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "090f9bb2_8a05cbd9",
        "filename": "docs/ANDROID-EMULATION-LIBRARY.TXT",
