      },
      "lineNbr": 185,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000411
      },
      "writtenOn": "2015-09-21T09:57:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, that\u0027s the idea. I think we should always rebuild both engines at the same time, caching as much as possible to keep things fast. It\u0027s the best way to avoid hidden build breaks.\n\nI\u0027ve completely rewritten that part of the document. Please take a look at the last section now.",
      "parentUuid": "e99c0776_2069f431",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 185,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 185,
        "endChar": 68
      },
      "revId": "b045c6127554eb0575023f042891a03d5e1e88f6",
